# Alembic migrations for the Sentinel Agent.

The database URL is read from the application configuration
(`Settings().storage.database_url`) at runtime -- see `env.py` -- so
the application and migrations share a single source of truth.

## Usage

```bash
# Create a new revision
poetry run alembic revision -m "describe the change"

# Apply pending revisions
poetry run alembic upgrade head

# Roll back one revision
poetry run alembic downgrade -1
```

No migration files exist yet. `alembic upgrade head` against an empty
`versions/` directory is a no-op that succeeds cleanly.
